Popular comedian Mr Macaroni has stated he will die the day he fails to advocate for a for better Nigeria. He spoke few hours after he condemned former Vice President Atiku Abubakar for deleting a post flaying the killing of Deborah Samuel for allegedly insulting Prophet Mohammed.   Tems’ voice connects with my soul, says American…     Alleged blasphemy: Macaroni blasts Atiku over deleted tweet     Ex-lover: Nobody said anything when Nkechi Blessing called…   The skit maker wrote::”I said on National TV today; that the day I Debo Adedayo will stop speaking up against injustice and oppression or stop advocating for a better nation is the day I die. This cause is perhaps the greatest reason for my existence and I am grateful that this is my path.”